@startuml Process Linking - Bilateral Crash Propagation

title Process Linking: Bilateral Crash Propagation

participant Main as main
participant "Proc A" as procA
participant "Proc B" as procB
participant ProcLink as link

== Setup ==

main -> procA: spawn(init, handler)
procA -> procA: message loop running

main -> procB: spawn(init, handler)
procB -> procB: message loop running

main -> link: link(procA, procB)
note right of link
  Installs mutual crash callbacks
  both ← onCrash handlers
end note
link -> procA: onCrash callback
link -> procB: onCrash callback

== Crash Propagation ==

procA -> procA: exception in handler
procA -> procA: lastError = exception
procA -> procA: exit message loop

procA -> procB: onCrash callback fires
note right of procA
  Bilateral: procB will also crash
  unless it traps exits
end note
procB -> procB: interrupt() virtual thread
procB -> procB: InterruptedException
procB -> procB: exit message loop

alt procB traps exits
  procA -> procB: deliver ExitSignal message
  procB -> procB: handle signal in mailbox
  note right of procB
    If trapExits=true:
    process stays alive
    can handle the signal
  end note
else procB does not trap exits
  procB -> main: propagates to supervisor
  note right of procB
    Crash cascades up to parent
    Supervisor restarts if configured
  end note
end

main -> main: both processes crashed
note right of main
  This is "let it crash" design
  Supervisor restarts failed children
end note
